definitions.definition: The waste that remains after the minerals have been extracted from an ore by ore dressing ; the waste from coal mining.
The weak feints , the last fraction of product obtained at the end of distillation , typically impure and containing fusel oils .
Inferior or damaged grain, as well as seeds of other plants (weeds), removed from grain before milling or sowing.
